<dl id="n08049a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08049a">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08049a"> 49(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> L writes R <font color="green">[figs]</font> / in mirror / ali&eacute;n&eacute; / trouble of sight / attempted calligraphy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Ne pas confondre l&apos;&eacute;criture artificielle avec l&apos;&eacute;criture des gauchers, l&apos;&eacute;criture en miroir, l&apos;&eacute;criture calligraphique des insignifiants, ni avec le graphisme des ali&eacute;n&eacute;s et des malades dans les troubles de la vue. <br><font color="green">[Do not confuse artificial writing with the writing of those who are left-handed, with mirror-writing, the calligraphic writing of nonentities, or with that of the insane or of the visually impaired.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 278</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: 278, the right hand page facing the citation above, exhibits example of handwriting above the heading &lsquo;Fig. 155&rsquo;. </mm> </dd></dl>
